Introduction¶

In this project I will be analyzing the data asscoiated with TDMB dataset from Kaggle. It is a dataset that contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue.. etc.

Questions to be analyzed:¶

  • Which combination of Genres have the most/least votes? (vote_average)
  • Which combination of Genres have the most/least popularity?

If we calculated the profit (revenue - budget) we can also ask:

  • What is the most/least profitable genres?
  • Which year has the most/least profitable movies?
  • What is the relationship between runtime and positive profit earnings?

Data assessment summary:¶

  • One duplicate
  • The columns:id, imdb_id, cast, homepage, director, tagline, keywords, overview, budget_adj, revenue_adj are unimportant and need to be dropped
  • Missing data in: genres, revenue, budget, production companies
  • Profit column needed

Data Cleaning (Applying the changes needed according to the data assessment above)¶

  • Remove duplicates
  • Drop unnecessary columns (id, imdb_id, cast, homepage, director, tagline, keywords, overview, budget_adj, revenue_adj)
  • Fill/Remove missing values (genres, revenue, budget, production companies)
  • Profit column to be calculated (revenue - budget) and inserted

In [42]:
def genreMax(column):
    return df[df[column] == max(df[column])][["genres", 'original_title', column]]

def genreMin(column):
    return df[df[column] == min(df[column])][["genres", 'original_title', column]]

Conclusions¶

Throughout this analysis I have tried to pose questions that would be useful to production companies.

From my figured out answers to those questions I have colncluded that the genres "Action and adventure" together are present in the:

  • Heighly voted
  • Most popular
  • Most profitable
    movies and so they are a vital dimension in the success of a movie.

Also from observing the profit gains across the release year its clear that there are no movies that brought significant profit after the 2012.

Limitations:¶

  1. Revenue and Budget didn't have specified currency
  2. Alot of missing data in Revenue and Budget columns and I had to drop alot of columns (which are vital to my case study)
  3. Missing some aspects about the movies like: movie language, scriptwriter, country of origin which could have been useful to our analysis
